Here's everything you need to know:How does South Korea compare with the U.S.?
In contrast, South Korea on April 2 had fewer than 10,000 confirmed cases and 169 deaths.
The difference is that South Korea sprang into action with early mass testing, tracking and isolating all contacts of those infected.
An outbreak of Middle East Respiratory Syndrome (MERS) in South Korea in 2015 exposed vulnerabilities that terrified the populace and forced an overhaul of epidemic response.
South Korea quickly surged its testing to some 20,000 people a day, but it also took more extreme measures.